.TH GIT-STAGE-BATCH-NEW 1 "May 2026" "git-stage-batch @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-stage-batch-new \- create a batch
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-stage-batch new
\fIBATCH\fR [\fB\-m\fR|\fB\-\-note\fR \fINOTE\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B new
creates an empty named batch that can later receive changes from
.BR include
or
.BR discard .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "\-m, \-\-note " NOTE
Set a description for the batch.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-stage-batch (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-list (1),
.BR git-stage-batch-include (1)
